  "response": "The duration of diarrhea can vary depending on the cause, but in most cases, it lasts for a few days. Acute diarrhea usually resolves within 2 to 3 days, while chronic diarrhea can last for more than 4 weeks. If diarrhea persists for more than a few days or is accompanied by severe symptoms, it's important to seek medical attention.",
